data.chText: （音乐、乐器、声乐等的）低音，低音部
data.enText: the lowest tone or part in music, for instruments or voices

data.chText: 他放立体声音响时总把低音调得很大。
data.enText: He always plays his stereo with the bass turned right up.
a man's singing voice with a low range; a man with a bass voice
a musical part that is written for a bass voice
an electric guitar that plays very low notes

data.chText: 低音电吉他和鼓的合奏
由杰基∙卡雷拉演奏低音吉他。

data.enText: the bass clef (= the symbol in music showing that the notes following it are low)

data.chText: 巴斯鱼（包括多种食用海鱼和淡水鱼）
data.enText: a sea or freshwater fish that is used for food

simple_means.memory_skill: bas 低，下；基础 + s → 低音的

means: (音乐、乐器、声乐等的)低音，低音部
巴斯鱼(包括多种食用海鱼和淡水鱼)

tr: nontechnical name for any of numerous edible marine and freshwater spiny-finned fishes
the member with the lowest range of a family of musical instruments
the lowest part of the musical range
the lowest adult male singing voice
the lowest part in polyphonic music
any of various North American freshwater fish with lean flesh (especially of the genus Micropterus)
the lean flesh of a saltwater fish of the family Serranidae
an adult male singer with the lowest voice
having or denoting a low vocal or instrumental range
example: a bass voice is lower than a baritone voice

value.boxr_value: Pronounced /beɪs/ for meanings 1 to 4, and /bæs/ for meaning 5. The plural of the noun in meaning 5 is bass. 义项1到4读作 /beɪs/，义项 5 读作 /bæs/，义项 5 的复数为 bass。

value.def: A bass is a man with a very deep singing voice.

example.tran: 伟大的俄罗斯男低音歌唱家夏利亚宾

value.def: A bass drum, guitar, or other musical instrument is one that produces a very deep sound.
In popular music, a bass is a bass guitar or a double bass .

example.ex: They had a bass and a piano and a sax and percussion.
example.tran: 他们有一把低音吉他、一架钢琴、一管萨克斯和打击乐器。

example.ex: ...Dave Ranson on bass and Kenneth Blevins on drums...
example.tran: 戴夫·兰森弹低音吉他，肯尼思·布莱文斯打鼓

example.ex: Kurt had started out playing bass in a rock band.
example.tran: 库尔特起初在一个摇滚乐队弹低音吉他。

value.def: On a stereo system or radio, the bass is the ability to reproduce the lower musical notes. The bass is also the knob which controls this.

example.ex: ...larger models which will then give more bass and a higher fidelity sound.
example.tran: 能够听到更多低音和高保真音效的更大的型号

value.tran: （立体声音响或收音机等的）低音部，低音部旋钮

value.def: Bass are edible fish that are found in rivers and the sea. There are several types of bass.

example.ex: They unloaded their catch of cod and bass.
example.tran: 他们把捕到的鳕鱼和鲈鱼卸下来。

posc.def: Bass is a piece of this fish eaten as food.

example.ex: ...a large fresh fillet of sea bass.
example.tran: 大块的新鲜海产鲈鱼片

trans: 大鼓，低音鼓(管弦乐队用)
鼓与贝司，鼓打贝司(20世纪90年代早期在英国出现的流行音乐舞曲，以快速鼓节奏和强劲缓慢的贝司节奏为特点)
低音提琴(尤为爵士乐乐师用语)

bas 低，下；基础 + e → 低下的
base 低，下；基础 + born 出生 → 出身卑微的
base 低，下；基础 + ment 具体物 → 地下室
base 低，下；基础 + ness 表状态 → 低下，卑微
bas 低，下；基础 + ic …的 → 基础的
bas 低，下；基础 + is 表性质 → 基础
bas 低，下；基础 + s → 低音的
de 使… + base 降低 → 降低；使卑下
sub 下 + base 基础 → 基层；基地
